# Single source of truth for Homebrew packages, tracked by chezmoi.
#
# Consumed by:
#   - run_onchange_install-brew-packages.sh.tmpl  (via the {{ "{{ template ... }}" }} directive)
#   - the `brewdiff` helper                        (to show drift vs. installed)
#
# Only HIGH-LEVEL packages are listed (formulae installed on request, i.e. what
# `brew bundle dump` emits) — transitive dependencies are omitted on purpose,
# since `brew` reinstalls them automatically. Regenerate/compare with `brewdiff`.
#
# macOS-only entries (casks, App Store apps, mac-specific brews/taps) are guarded
# by an OS check so this renders to a clean, linuxbrew-safe file on Linux.
# Homebrew casks are macOS-only by definition, so they all live in that block.
#
# Workflow:
#   brewdiff        # show what's installed but not tracked here (and vice versa)
#   then edit this file to add what you want to keep, and `chezmoi apply`.

